Package org.neuroph.contrib.neat.gen

Interface Summary
Gene A Gene represents some "genetic material" inside an Organism.
Innovation Any class that implements this Innovation interface should have it's creation recorded in the Innovations.
NeatParameters NeatParameters defines the environment and the algorithm to use for a NEAT process.
NeuralNetworkBuilder Simple builder interface for creating an instance of NeuralNetwork from an Organism.
TerminationCondition Simple interface that is used by the Evolver to determine when the evolutionary process should be halted.
 

Class Summary
ConnectionGene A ConnectionGene represents a connection between two NeuronGenes.
Evolver Evolver is the main class that performs the NEAT evolutionary process.
FitnessScores A simple cache that stores all of the fitness scores for the evolutionary process.
Generation A Generation is a snapshot of the Species at the end of each generation.
Innovations The Innovations is a simple class that monitors the creation of ConnectionGene and NeuronGenes as part of the evolution process.
NeuronGene A NeuronGene is a type of Gene that represents a Neuron in the NeuralNetwork.
Organism An Organism is a member of the genetic population that is responsible for creating a NeuralNetowork.
Specie A Specie represents a collection of Organisms that are deemed similar by the Speciator.
 

Enum Summary
EvolutionEventType A EvolutionEventType is sent to all instances of
NeuronType Simple enumeration that represents the type of a NeuronGene.
 

Exception Summary
NeatException A simple Exception that is raised when there is a problem with NEAT.
